                <h2>About this recipe</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Source: </b> From <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1941631045/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&creative=9325&creativeASIN=1941631045">Plant Powered Familes by Dreena Burton (Amazon)</a>, Best Banan Bread (page 48)</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="planning">
                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> X minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 43-48 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 1 loaf (12 muffins) <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Loaf pan</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>

                    
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Whole-grain spelt flour, 1 cups  + 3-4 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>Oat flour, 3/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Baking powder, 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking soda, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Cinnamon, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Ground Nutmeg, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Sea salt, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Pureed overrip banana, 1 cup</li>
                    <li>Plain non-dairy milk, 1/2 cup</li>
                    <li>Maple syrup, 1/3 cup</li>
                    <li>Vanilla extract, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>[Optional] Chocolate chips, 3-4 Tbsp</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 350deg</li>
                    <li>In large bowl combine flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and sea salt</li>
                    <li>In a medium bowl, combine pureed bananas, milk, maple syrup, and vanilla   mix all together</li>
                    <li>Fold the wet mixture into the dry mixture, stirring until just combined</li>
                    <li>Add the chocolate chips and stir</li>
                    <li>Put in loaf pan</li>
                    <li>Bake for 43-48 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean</li>
                    
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Can also be made into muffins - bake for 17-20 minutes</li>
                    
                </ul>

            </div>

            <div id="Nutrition">
                <h2>Nutritition per serving</h2>
